'''Mike Vosburg''' is a comic book illustrator who worked on a few issues of the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] comic series.

His work in comics began in the 1970s were he worked on several underground comics, and in the late 1970s and 1980s worked regularly on some [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] and [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]] as well as co-creating the series ''Lori Lovecraft''. Vosburg has also contributed to television and films with his illustrations, including work on the [[Wikipedia:HBO|HBO]] series [[Wikipedia:Tales from the Crypt (TV series)|''Tales from the Crypt'']] where he did storyboarding and illustrating the comic covers used in the series. He also produced the storyboards for the [[2005]] film adaptation of [[Wikipedia:The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe|''The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe'']].

